  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop your <strong>ginger</strong>,<strong> shallots</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong>, then roughly chop your <strong>coriander</strong>, including the stalks</p><p>Bash your<strong> lemongrass stalk[s] </strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers </strong>and<strong> </strong>set aside for later, then chop the<strong> softer inner core[s]</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-5-1679404276895-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-5-1679404276895-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-5-1679404276895-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-5-1679404276895-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-5-1679404276895-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>,<strong> chopped lemongrass </strong>and <strong>coriander </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> with your<strong> ground paprika</strong>, <strong>cracked black pepper</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> soy sauce</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> vegetable oil</strong>, 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and 1.5 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and blitz to a paste – this is your<strong> fiery curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-5-1679404287401-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-5-1679404287401-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-5-1679404287401-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-5-1679404287401-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-5-1679404287401-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and the <strong>outer</strong> <strong>lemongrass layers<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and stir vigorously for 1 min, then cover and cook for 12-15 min or until the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove the pot from the heat and discard the<strong> outer lemongrass layers</strong> and keep covered until serving – this is your<strong> lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-5-1679404453194-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-5-1679404453194-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-5-1679404453194-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-5-1679404453194-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-5-1679404453194-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chicken breast </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for an initial 4-5 min on each side or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-5-1679404457625-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-5-1679404457625-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-5-1679404457625-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-5-1679404457625-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-5-1679404457625-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Separate the<strong> onion wedges</strong> into petals</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1679404465831-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1679404465831-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1679404465831-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1679404465831-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1679404465831-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken<strong> </strong>is browned, add the <strong>halved green beans</strong> and<strong> onion petals</strong> and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the veg has started to soften and the chicken is golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1679404475867-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1679404475867-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1679404475867-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1679404475867-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1679404475867-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>fiery curry paste</strong> and cook for 4-5 min, stirring to coat everything in the paste – this is your <strong>chicken breast pad prik king</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1679404485389-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1679404485389-x400.jpg",
